# Segment gates (Cursor agent)

- Implement **one bounded segment** at a time. Keep commits **atomic** to that segment only.
- After code changes, run **`npm run segment:gates -- --segment "<id>"`**. Add **`--ui`** when routes, layouts, or visual behavior changed (requires dev server + Playwright; see `docs/agent-gates-runbook.md`).
- Treat **`test-results/agent-gates/*.json`** as proof of gate execution. Do not call work “done” without a PASS artifact when gates apply.
- Use **conventional commits** (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`). Follow playbooks under `agents/playbooks/` and handoff template `agents/templates/segment-handoff.md`.
- Prefer **`AGENTS.md`** and **`CODEX.md`** for stack-specific commands; this repo uses **npm** (not Bun) for the same script contract.
- **Loop continuity** (BOOT / FIND / RECORD between sessions): **`docs/Autonomous.md`**.
